'''Aron Elias Seligmann''', ''baron von Eichthal'', (26 April 1747 – 11 January 1824) was a [[Ashkenazi Jews|German Jewish]] financier. He served as [[Court Jew]] for [[Charles Theodore, Elector of Bavaria|Charles Theodore]] and [[Maximilian I Joseph of Bavaria]].<ref>{{cite journal |last=Ratcliffe |first=Barrie M. |title=Crisis and Identity: Gustave d'Eichthal and Judaism in the Emancipation Period |journal=[[Jewish Social Studies]] |volume=37 |issue=2 |year=1975 |pages=122–140 |jstor=4466874 }}</ref> After converting to Catholicism he was ennobled in 1814 as ''Freiherr von Eichthal''.<ref>{{cite book |title=Genealogisches Handbuch des Adels |series=Adelslexikon |volume=61 |page=106 |publisher=C. A. Starke Verlag |location=Limburg (Lahn) |year=1975 }}</ref>

