The '''Department of Civil Aviation of Lao PDR''' is the [[civil aviation authority]] of [[Laos]].<ref>"[http://www.icao.int/safety/fsix/lpcompliance1/2008/Laos_en.pdf English Language Proficiency]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6N1jWkSBd Archive]) Department of Civil Aviation. Retrieved on 30 January 2014.</ref> The agency, a division of the [[Ministry of Public Works and Transport (Laos)|Ministry of Public Works and Transport]], has its headquarters on the property of the [[Wattay International Airport]] in [[Sikhodtabong District]], [[Vientiane]].<ref>"[http://www.faa.gov/air_traffic/publications/ifim/country_info/PDF/la.pdf Laos]" ([https://www.webcitation.org/6N1ngmsNV Archive]). [[Federal Aviation Administration]]. p. 2/10. "Ministry of Public Works and Transport Department of Civil Aviation Vientiane/Wattay International Airport P.O. Box 119 Vientiane, Lao PDR."</ref>

